{
  "texts": [
    "The inference cost of LLMs is high: Although generative language models support input dynamic context, the computational cost of generating long texts or complex answers in real-time scenarios is still high, making it difficult to achieve true real-time response.",
    "From the perspective of a user in fast-moving domains, perceiving answers as out-of-date or unsafe would rapidly erode trust in decision-support systems.",
    "On the other hand, pursuing real-time performance leads to latency spikes, which reduces conversational fluidity.",
    "As a result, users may abandon interactions.",
    "Overhead and time complexity 1."
  ]
}